title: For Sale/Trade:  Original type 2 WWII Luminous Disc for trade. 101st Airborne
location: 1 hour North of Seattle, Seattle, Washington
postcontent:
Truely the must have holy grail of any serious WWII collector. I have for sale a genuine luminous disc issued to NCO's and officers of the 101st airborne on D-Day. If you are reading this, it is still available.

It was supposed to aid in re-grouping at night as it used to glow in the dark. It is a must for re-enactors that want an authentic uniform and gear loadout. The phoshorus compund has worn out, but the Radium component is still very radioactive.

This is NOT a relic grade piece dug up in a field like 90% you see. It is all original with 80% of the original blueing still in tact. Some poor guy carried this through the whole war and eventually ended up back here in the U.S.

It is a U.S. issue type two which can be either clipped onto your clothing or helmet webbing with the rivetted on clip, or tied on by means of two holes. It is marked POISON INSIDE. This is the rarest of all PERSONAL luminous disc markers and it is valued in the $750 range at auction.

Comes in a custom locking yellow shielded .50 cal ammo can with proper transport markings. It is perfectly safe and legal to own. It is also the single most radioactive thing in the world you can buy without a license, thus the shielded can. 

Appointments and pictures available by Email only. Prefer to trade for russian semi-auto's or a S&W .38 +P capable revolver.

First off I must say this firearm has been great to me I carried it daily for over a year it has never let me down is a great shooter and is in overall great condition for a carry gun. So you may wonder what makes this gun so rare. well there are many first gen 247s out there it is fairly common for the full frame versions to have a built in decocking system it is far more uncommon for the compact versions to have such a feature this will allow you to decock it after loading a round in the chamber there for carrying it with a double action trigger for more peace of mind. very limited versions they put a titanium slide on the 247 now what makes this firearm rare is that it is the compact version with a titanium slide and decocker system. so what you have is a striker fired pistol capable of being decocked  in the compact lighter version with the titanium slide. Acording to taurus it looks like 2009 was the only year they made this guy with those 3 combinations in a very limited run of numbers. go ahead look for yourself will be very hard hard to find 1. in all the time I've had this gun I've only seen 1 with titanium and ds but it was a full frame.
